<!-- rnb-source-begin  -->

```r
by_year <- gapminder_data %>%
  group_by(year,continent) %>%
  summarize(mean_gdpPercap = mean(gdpPercap),
            max_gdpPercap = max(gdpPercap),
            median_gdpPercap = median(gdpPercap),
            min_gdpPercap = min(gdpPercap))
```

<!-- rnb-source-end -->

<!-- rnb-output-begin eyJkYXRhIjoiYHN1bW1hcmlzZSgpYCBoYXMgZ3JvdXBlZCBvdXRwdXQgYnkgJ3llYXInLiBZb3UgY2FuIG92ZXJyaWRlIHVzaW5nIHRoZSBgLmdyb3Vwc2AgYXJndW1lbnQuXG4ifQ== -->

```
`summarise()` has grouped output by 'year'. You can override using the `.groups` argument.
```



<!-- rnb-output-end -->

<!-- rnb-source-begin  -->

```r
ggplot(by_year, aes(x = year, y = mean_gdpPercap, color = continent)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_line() + 
  labs(title = "Durchschnittlicher BIP/Kopf im verlaufe der Jahre",
       x = "Jahre",
       y = "BIP/Kopf",
       subtitle = "60 Observationen",
       caption = "Gapminder",
       color = "Kontinente") 
```

byafrica <- by_year %>% filter(continent == "Africa")

ggplot(byafrica, aes(x = year, y = mean_gdpPercap)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_line() + 
  geom_area(alpha = 0.2, fill = "red") + 
  ylim(0, 30000) + 
  labs(title = "Durchschnittlicher BIP/Kopf im verlaufe der Jahre",
       x = "Jahre",
       y = "BIP/Kopf",
       subtitle = "Afrika",
       caption = "12 Observationen")
